  "title": "Bewitching Devil",
  "secondName": "Bewitching Devil",
  "description": "The autumn harvest festival. Children flock to the streets, dressed as evil spirits to protect themselves from the real evil. A single grown woman can be seen among them, however, her body and mind differ greatly in age. Though an adult in appearance, in spirit she's no different than the children pestering passers-by for treats. It is no surprise, then, that she too wanted to wear a costume—even if she couldn't quite find the right size.\n\"How do I look, Mama? If you don't say 'cute', I will play a trick on you...!\"",
